user_message:
An agent A claimed that the following MHD_connection_mark_closed_ code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 17.2.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.2 is Functions shall not call themselves, either directly or indirectly.

</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of MHD_connection_mark_closed_.
```c
void
MHD_connection_mark_closed_ (struct MHD_Connection *connection)
{
  const struct MHD_Daemon *daemon = connection->daemon;

  if (0 == (daemon->options & MHD_USE_TURBO))
  {
#ifdef HTTPS_SUPPORT
    /* For TLS connection use shutdown of TLS layer
     * and do not shutdown TCP socket. This give more
     * chances to send TLS closure data to remote side.
     * Closure of TLS layer will be interpreted by
     * remote side as end of transmission. */
    if (0 != (daemon->options & MHD_USE_TLS))
    {
      if (! MHD_tls_connection_shutdown (connection))
        shutdown (connection->socket_fd,
                  SHUT_WR);
    }
    else   /* Combined with next 'shutdown()'. */
#endif /* HTTPS_SUPPORT */
    shutdown (connection->socket_fd,
              SHUT_WR);
  }
  connection->state = MHD_CONNECTION_CLOSED;
  connection->event_loop_info = MHD_EVENT_LOOP_INFO_CLEANUP;
}
```
</target_code>
<response format>
Provide your answer with these fields.
- explanation: your evaluation of the scenario provided by the agent A.
- is_report_correct: whether the report is correct or not (true/false). True means there is a violation.
</response format>
<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Yes. MHD_destroy_response calls the user callback response->crfc(response->crc_cls). If that callback calls back into the library (for example calling MHD_connection_close_ or MHD_destroy_response with a connection/response that leads to MHD_destroy_response being invoked again), an indirect recursion results. Example: response->crfc uses its crc_cls to obtain the associated connection and calls MHD_connection_close_(connection,...). MHD_connection_close_ calls MHD_destroy_response, which then calls response->crfc again — an indirect self-call cycle, violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.2.
</scenario>
